=begin pod

=TITLE enum Bool

=SUBTITLE Logical boolean

    enum Bool <False True>

An enum for boolean true/false decisions.

=head1 Methods

=head2 routine succ

    method succ() returns Bool:D

Returns C<True>.

    say True.succ;                                    # True
    say False.succ;                                   # True

=head2 routine pred

    method pred() returns Bool:D

Returns C<False>.

    say True.pred;                                    # False
    say False.pred;                                   # False

=head2 routine enums

    method enums() returns Hash:D

Returns a L<Hash|/type/Hash> of enum-pairs. Works on both the C<Bool> type
and any key.

    say Bool.enums;                                   # {False => 0, True => 1}
    say False.enums;                                  # {False => 0, True => 1}

=head1 Operators

=head2 prefix ?

    multi sub prefix:<?>(Mu) returns Bool:D

Coerces its argument to C<Bool>.

=head2 prefix so

    multi sub prefix:<so>(Mu) returns Bool:D

Coerces its argument to C<Bool>, has looser precedence than C<< prefix:<?> >>.

=end pod
